It's a bug in Java 8. See https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8040892 for details. It was fixed in Java 9.

@junit-team/junit-lambda shall we roll our own `toMap` helper and always emit a helpful error message?

```
	private Map<String, String> map(List<KeyValuePair> pairs) {
		Map<String, String> map = new HashMap<>();
		for (KeyValuePair pair : pairs) {
			String key = pair.key;
			if (map.containsKey(key)) {
				Exception cause = new IllegalStateException("Duplicate key " + key + " in: " + pairs);
				throw new JUnitException("Error parsing command-line arguments", cause);
			}
			map.put(key, pair.value);
		}
		return map;
	}
```
